<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-3295] BitVector never skips fully populated bytes when writing ClearedDgaps</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3295</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;When writing cleared DGaps in BitVector we compare a byte against 0xFF (255) yet the byte is casted into an int (-1) and the comparison will never succeed. We should mask the byte with 0xFF before comparing or compare against -1&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
            <key id="12513267">LUCENE-3295</key>
            <summary>BitVector never skips fully populated bytes when writing ClearedDgaps</summary>
